# GitGuardian ignore — Aegis is an on-device privacy classifier.
# The repo intentionally contains content shaped like sensitive material
# so the classifier can learn to recognize it. None of it is real:
#   - samples/                 30-file eval corpus across 4 verdict
#                              classes. Includes synthetic .env files,
#                              k8s Secret YAMLs, PEM keys, and
#                              placeholder service-account JSON.
#   - samples/external/        Files mined from public GitHub repos
#                              via tools/sample_collector.py. The
#                              source files are already public; this
#                              repo didn't introduce them to the world.
#   - train/curated_data.py    200 hand-curated training examples.
#                              50 are deliberately shaped like leaked
#                              credentials so the classifier learns
#                              to flag them.
#   - aegis-head/              Serialized trained-classifier weights
#                              (LR head). 25 KB joblib file; not
#                              credential material, but excluded for
#                              completeness.
#
# Everything outside these paths is still scanned normally.

samples/**
samples/external/**
train/curated_data.py
train/dataset.jsonl
aegis-head/**
